The article provides a list of individuals who were invited to sit in the First Lady's box at the State of the Union Address. The list includes Sergeant Sheena Adams, Alan Aleman, Jack Andraka, Susan Bumgarner, Deb Carey, Sergeant Carlos Evans, Tim Cook, Cleopatra Cowley-Pendleton and Nathaniel A. Pendleton Sr., Menchu de Luna Sanchez, Bobak Ferdowsi, Bradley Henning, Tracey Hepner, Peter Hudson, Governor John Kitzhaber, Mayor Marie Lopez Rogers, Amanda E. McMillan, Lee Maxwell, Lieutenant Brian Murphy, Lisa Richards, Kaitlin Roig, Abby Schanfield, Haile Thomas, Desiline Victor. Each individual has their own story and accomplishments.